I really, really enjoyed the super truck worm, and the backstory behind the anomaly. It felt cool, unique, and elegantly simple at the same time.

However, I feel the last addendum doesn't work well as an ending.  is such an obvious consequence of how the truck worm acts that it isn't a cool ending. The wife revealing that he started melting as soon as he was put in the ground is much more dramatic, and so putting the less interesting news report after feels anti-climactic. I think the last addendum should either be moved earlier than the interview, made into a footnote, or removed entirely.







