I'd heard this one mentioned a few times before I finally got around to reading it, and I'll admit I was expecting this to be a pretty straight-forward haha funny sort of article- I was actually very positively surprised to see that wasn't quite the case. That's not to say this isn't pretty funny (it is) but there's also some great dialogue and a really good narrative here. I like the open-endedness of the implications in the addenda as well- there's just enough unsaid to leave me thinking about it without feeling unsatisfying or vague. Good truck worm all around, easy +1 for a fun-to-read, solidly self-contained piece!







